snippet.textDisplay: The lesson I got from this is that many of us may go on to live well into our years, but we should never forget that anything can happen at anytime to cause our departure or the departure of those we love to be untimely. We will all die, no matter how long we manage to live; but Kobe's and Gigi's deaths forces us to accept the reality that we can die at the most unexpected times and there is nothing anybody can do about it. Yes, it does seem unfair, like Kobe was supposed to live another 40+ years, but this warped tragedy has forced us to accept that nothing is promised. One minute you're going about your day, and the next, the coroner is dissecting your body. It's very morbid.

snippet.textDisplay: For those of you saying that the reason that Kobe's parents didn't like Vanessa because she was Latina, that is a lie. First of all she is of mixed races she is also Irish. Anyway,  the Bryant family has plenty of non black members. His parents were against the marriage because Kobe was 21, a grown man and Vanessa was a teenager of 17 years old in high school. He met her on a video shoot and she was a "video girl". I'm not going to use the other word because she is going through a lot. But we all know what that term is. And if you saw the video, like I did back in the day, then you would see she was doing too much and dressed way older than a 17 year old should. Allegedly her stepfather/mother pretty much made them get married because she was so young and Kobe had money which is why it went so quickly, 6 months after they met. And there were no statutory rape charges filed. Her stepfather, that raised her, has openly called her a gold digger and stated that she was taught that by her own mother. The Bryant family has never did multiple interviews talking negatively about her. But her own family has. She was still in high school and completed the rest with independent study. Then she waited 10 years and filed for divorce because she knew she would get money. Vanessa has not started any business nor did anything successful on her own, like other professional athletes wives have,  she has had several lawsuits filed against her because of how she treats staff, which have been settled out of court, and according to other professional athlete's wives, she isn't the friendliest person nor nicest to deal with. Kobe's parents were concerned for that reason. Then when he had all of the affairs, with multiple women and assault charges,  people saw that it was not some "love story". So please stop it with the racist talk. Everything isn't about race. How would you feel as a parent if your talented, millionaire grown son that you put through school and gave the best life was dating a child in high school that was doing nothing in life? Which is illegal by the way in California. Again, nothing to do with race.

snippet.textDisplay: We do not know the day or time that we will leave this world, I just know that we must be 100% united with our parents and parents with their children.
